# M-001 Project Foundation

**Release:** v0.1 Foundation

**Status:** ✅ Complete

---

# Objective

Transform Cougar from an idea into a structured engineering project.

---

# Why This Milestone Mattered

Before software can scale, the project itself must have structure.

This milestone focused on creating the engineering foundation required for long-term development rather than immediately building features.

---

# Engineering Work

Completed:

- Defined Cougar OS as the primary platform.
- Established long-term engineering direction.
- Organized the project into a scalable structure.
- Created development standards.
- Began treating Cougar as a production software platform.

---

# Engineering Decisions

The following principles were established:

- Documentation-first engineering
- Modular architecture
- Enterprise-first design
- Long-term scalability over rapid feature delivery
- Engineering discipline over rapid prototyping

---

# Outcome

Cougar officially transitioned from a software concept into a structured engineering initiative.

Future releases would build upon this foundation.

